# Local notes only. Production secrets via:
#   npx wrangler secret put …
#
# Auth MVP: magic-link tokens live in D1; verify URL is returned in API
# response until an email provider is wired (Resend / Email Workers / etc.).
#
# Local stack (two processes — not one command with +):
#   Terminal A: npm run dev:api    # Worker + D1 + R2 on :8787
#   Terminal B: npm run dev        # Astro; /api and /media proxied to :8787
# Or one shot:  npm run dev:all
#
# R2: wrangler.toml binds MEDIA → dimela-mx-media.
# Local wrangler simulates the bucket. For remote deploy, enable R2 in the
# Cloudflare Dashboard, then:
#   npx wrangler r2 bucket create dimela-mx-media
#
# Demo login emails (seeded):
#   Member: romina@tortilla.studio  → /editar/
#   Admin:  hola@dimela.mx          → /admin/
#
# R2: MEDIA binding in wrangler.toml (dimela-mx-media). Upload API exists;
# wire /editar/ UI next. Local media URLs need Worker (:8787 / deploy), not Astro alone.
#
# Later: AUTH_SECRET, Stripe keys, email OTP provider, etc.
